-- Euro Extends Gain as Draghi Says Credit Enhancement Discussed
-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 2013-05-02T12:39:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-02/euro-extends-gain-as-draghi-says-credit-enhancement-discussed.html
The euro extended an advance against
the yen after European Central Bank President  Mario Draghi  said
the bank took decisions on ways to enhance credit at a meeting
in Bratislava.  The euro gained 1.1 percent to 129.76 yen as of 1:38 p.m.
London time. It rose 0.1 percent to $1.3194.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucy Meakin in London at 
